    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/criminology/CRM/206.html" title="CRM 206 - Race, Ethnicity and Justice" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRM 206</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Race, Ethnicity and Justice</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course explores the connections between racialization and criminalization. Students are introduced to critical anti-racist and anti-colonialist perspectives on the role of race/ethnicity - and its intersection with gender, sexuality, class and age - in shaping social, political and legal ways of understanding 'crime' and 'justice'. We consider a range of avenues through which people and spaces are racialized and linked to crime as well as the possibility of using the law to obtain social justice.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
