		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces students to the ethical foundations of justice, and their implications and applications at various junctures in the criminal justice system. Ethics in public and private policing, the legal profession (defense, prosecution, judiciary), and punishment are given in-depth consideration.  Emphasis will be placed on a case study approach, and student-led analyses.</div>
	
	
