		<div class="courseListDescription">This course introduces the students to some traditional as well as non-traditional security threats currently challenging Canada and the global community. Students will critically evaluate such topics as transnational organized crime, international terrorism, human trafficking, money laundering and drug trafficking in order to assess the effectiveness of current legal and non-legal methods in dealing with these phenomena.</div>
	
	
